    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add your <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!)<strong> </strong>to a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix thoroughly until fully combined (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Divide and shape them into 6 meatballs per person</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-marinara-flatbreads/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> in 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>warm water</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> dried oregano</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and your<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> marinara sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-marinara-flatbreads/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-marinara-flatbreads/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>naan[s]</strong> to a baking tray</p><p>Spread 1/3 of the <strong>marinara sauce</strong> over each <strong>naan </strong>in a thin layer and top with the <strong>meatballs</strong> and <strong>torn mozzarella</strong></p><p>Put the <strong>loaded</strong> <strong>naan[s]</strong> in the oven for 15 min or until the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!) and the mozzarella is melted and golden \u2013 these are your <strong>meatball marinara flatbreads</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-marinara-flatbreads/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining marinara sauce</strong> and cook<strong> </strong>for<strong> </strong>2-3 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>marinara dip</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-marinara-flatbreads/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then rip into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-marinara-flatbreads/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>balsamic dressing</strong></p><p>Toss the <strong>torn lettuce</strong> and <strong>grated carrot</strong> with the <strong>balsamic dressing </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-meatball-marinara-flatbreads/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>meatball marinara flatbread </strong>alongside the <strong>salad </strong>and a pot of the <strong>marinara dip</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
